description: You are looking at a very well cared for 1982 Correct Craft SkiTique with the original Correct Craft Trailer. It is a privately owned boat being sold on consignment at Stressless Auto on behalf of the owner. Consignment sales give you the best of both worlds: you get a well cared for, privately owned car with a known history as well as the ease and security of working with a very service focused, specialty dealer. The Correct Craft SkiTique was a well renowned ski boat in the early 1980s -- it was really the cat's meow.  This is a two-owner boat, with both owners living here in Austin.  The first owner bought it at a boat show in 1982 here in town.  He sold it to the current owner, who collects classic cars and has taken every precaution to ensure this boat stays like new. This boat is all original, except for the bottom cushion on the two front seats.  It has the original Ford 302 V8 engine, original trailer, original gel coat, original carpet, and original vinyl.  It runs beautifully and is a lot of fun for a day on the lake. The trailer has good tires, new lights, and just passed a TX safety inspection. We are a licensed dealer, but most of our business comes from consulting and consignment sales. The price above does not include TT&L. The Play is the most versatile kayak available today! Designed for smaller, shorter paddlers and kids the Play is also great kayak for paddlers up to 200 lbs. At only 31 lbs the Play is lightweight and compact, simple to transport, load and unload and can be quickly launched and easily maneuvered. Stability is provided by a shallow V-shaped hull that enhances maneuverability and tracking. The clean deck design, comfortable cockpit area and rounded ergonomic shapes make it easy to use. Three different foot positions for different length legs make it an excellent choice for sharing by the whole family or a group of friends. Its got the upgraded 5.0 motor and a couple of add ons such as a wakeboard tower etc. I understand its dirty in the pics but Id be happy to pay for a detail for someone serious and take it out on the lake for a test drive. This is a good find for someone to take advantage of. If you are serious, call me and talk to me please don't just ask a bunch of random questions. Call 830-632-678five text- 909-496-839two

description: 1997 Sunesta Deck boat, 350cid rebuilt with approx. 200hrs. Mechanically sound, interior needs to be replaced, no prop, or battery, Comes with tandem axle trailer, bimini top. A little TLC and you'll have an awesome boat, considering a new boat of this type starts on the bottom around $60k.

description: 1985 COBALT 21' Bow Rider - $5800 This is a well-built classic boat. They do not build them like this anymore without spending lots of $. Trailer is a 2010 in great condition very few miles on it. Boat has only 564 hrs. Runs Great and very good condition. Deep hull has great ride in all conditions. If it's a windy day and you want to go out no worries. LOTS of cabin space no matter where you sit you're not cramped. Lots of storage. Rear Bench folds down to make a bed and front has center cushion to make a sun deck. Plenty of power from 5.7 - 260 HP (Chevy 350) Runs perfect, strong no smoke no leaks. All fluids and filters just replaced. Comes with: New Bluetooth Stereo, 4 New Composite Speakers and waterproof remote. description: We are highly dedicated to our Customers. We specialize in Boat and RV Detailing, Fiberglass, Kevlar,Aluminum. We also Detail everything in the Automotive World. Boating Season is upon us once again. Time to get your watercraft,RV detailed and looking GREAT for the Summer Season. Protecting your investment and helping retain the value. Full service detailing,Wet Sanding, Oxidation Removal, Hull Cleaning, Acid Washing Pontoons, Barnacle removal, Mineral Deposits, Black Mold removal, Spider as well as Bird Dropping removal, Hard Water Spots, Carpet Shampoo. These things can be done at a fair and competitive price. Not the cheapest, but not the highest either. Quality Work at a Fair Price. Local Boat Dealerships use our service, San Antonio, Austin, Pflugerville. Have photos as well as references. Only use Name Brand Products, 3M, Meguiar's, Mary Kate, Mothers. Example of a typical detail is as follows: Pressure Wash, Hand Wash, Cleaner Wax, Polymer Sealant, Vinyl Clean and Condition, Vacuum Interior, Wipe down under seats, Clean Windshield, Shine SS Cleats, Hand Rails, Spray off Boat cover, Wash Trailer, Tire Dressing if applicable. Pricing is based on overall Condition of your craft. We offer pick up service at a fair price, or can come to your location. The Boat dealerships have a 6 week wait for service work, so get the boat detailed while waiting. Please don't hesitate in contacting us with questions or to schedule an appointment. Due to spam and internet hackers, please respond to this ad with your Name and Contact information and I will contact you ASAP. Thank you for your time as well as considering us for Services.
title: Fall Boating and RV Season

description: Low hours for the age of the boat stored for 6 years and barely used until moving to the lake only took out two or three times a month the last four years 220 horse power fish finder included as well as Bimini top
title: 06 Tahoe fish an ski

description: Prior to August, this jetski ran well. In August, we adjusted the carburetor to get rid of a flat spot in the throttle. When I tested it, it ran great up to about 40 mph and then bogged. I turned around to bring it in for more adjustment and it died with a thunk and wouldn't restart. We found that the engine is "locked up." I later realized that we adjusted the carburetor with the fuel switch off. Although I hate to get rid of it, I'm selling this jetski for parts and am including the trailer. This is a 3-seater and was a blast to ride with plenty of power to pull boarders or skiers! I have the title in hand. Both the trailer and jetski have some cosmetic damage: for example, dings, scratches, sun damage, but functionally they are good except for the locked up engine. The trailer has a long tongue which makes it much easier to back. If you don't like my asking price, please make me an offer. Repair history in last 4 years (receipts available): May, 2014: New used pump, wear rings and impeller June, 2014: Replaced impeller with propeller. Works great! Nov, 2014: Replaced one cylinder, new spark plugs Aug, 2016: Motor "locked up"
title: REDUCED! 1997 Polaris SLT780 jetski and trailer
